{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Cut the top of the garlic bulb to expose the top of garlic cloves, then place garlic bulb in a casserole dish. Bake for 35-40 minutes (180°C). Meanwhile continue with recipe.","Place 20 g olive oil and onions in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>, then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place honey, wholegrain mustard, Dijon mustard, garlic cloves, fresh rosemary and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl then chop <strong><b>8 sec\/speed 8<b><\/strong>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Chop again <strong><b>5 sec\/speed 8<b><\/strong>.","Transfer reserved sautéed onions to the casserole dish with the garlic head, place the chicken breasts on the onions and pour over the honey-mustard mixture. Bake for 25-30 minutes (180°C). Meanwhile clean and dry mixing bowl, then continue with recipe.","Place 400 g cauliflower florets in mixing bowl and chop <strong><b>15 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 400 g cauliflower florets in mixing bowl and chop <strong><b>15 sec\/speed 5<b><\/strong>.","Add reserved chopped cauliflower, 15 g olive oil, milk, 1 tsp salt and ground pepper then cook <strong><b>20 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b><\/strong>.","Carefully remove the baked garlic bulb from the oven and squeeze it to extract the baked garlic cloves. Add baked garlic cloves to mixing bowl and blend <strong><b>1 min 30 sec\/speed 7<b><\/strong>. Serve chicken breasts with garlic-cauliflower purée, garnished with fresh thyme leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 garlic bulb","35 g olive oil","250 g onions, halved","30 g honey","40 g wholegrain mustard","10 g Dijon mustard              (optional)","2 garlic cloves","1 tbsp fresh rosemary, leaves only","2 tsp salt","4 chicken breast fillets (approx. 650 g)","800 g cauliflower florets","130 g milk","¼ - ½ tsp freshly ground pepper, to taste","1 tsp fresh thyme leaves"]}],"id":"r132538","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-vnk5CENmCZ0\/XZQxDJwhR0I\/AAAAAAAAcrI\/hymM4RqWby8q2b6AAcMfAo74wmPJ3-TrQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ksdLEoE71dTutHBs.png","title":"Honey Mustard Baked Chicken and Garlic-Cauliflower Purée","publishedAt":"2016-10-31T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"46 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17 g","calories":"1596 kJ \/ 381 kcal"},"usefulItems":"casserole dish, oven","basicInfo":["easy","15m","50m","4 portions"]}